article.headline: Coppin St 72, Hampton 65
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Coppin State overcame a one-point deficit at halftime to defeat Hampton 72-65 Monday night. Darryl Roberts scored a team-high 20 points for Coppin (4-12, 4-1 Mid-Eastern Atlantic Conference). Darryl Proctor and Talmadge Bell each contributed 12 points, and Proctor had a team-high nine rebounds. Jaz Cowan scored a game-high 30 points and grabbed a game-high 12 rebounds for Hampton (5-8, 4-2).
